Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art showing six quadruped animal figures pecked in outline including two giraffes and three others (cattle?), all upright and facing right. At the top left there is a small, faint outline of a giraffe. To the right of this is the figure of a short necked quadruped (cow?). To the lower right of this is a large central figure of a cow with long horns spread sideways. Below this are two further figures (cattle?), hornless. On the bottom figure the engraver appears to have made use of a natural rock formation to suggest an udder. To the right of these is the outline of a giraffe. These engravings are quite faint. A 5cm photo scale has been fitted at the base of the image. Wadi Anak, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
